All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Arrival
Represents the event of a vehicle arriving at a stop.
HistoryEntry
Represents an immutable instance of a vehicle arrival event at a stop.
Location
Represents a geographical location in the world.
PassengerLoad
A measure of how crowded a transit vehicle is, derived from the ratio of the current passenger count to the vehicle's total capacity.
PredictedArrival
Represents the predicted arrival of a vehicle at a stop.
PrtHistoryTable
Represents a collection of HistoryEntry instances, encapsulating data related to vehicle arrival events.
PrtInfo
A static utility class for fetching information about stops and routes in the Pittsburgh Regional Transit system.
PrtRealTime
A static utility class for fetching information from Pittsburgh Regional Transit's real-time data pool.
PrtSchedule
A static utility class that contains methods to get information related to the scheduled arrival of vehicles at stops.
PrtSchedule.Selector
Builder pattern that allows customized querying of schedule.
Route
Represents an immutable public transit route.
RouteDirection
Represents the different directions that vehicles operate on a route.
ScheduledArrival
Represents the scheduled arrival of a vehicle at a stop.
ScheduledTrip
Represents a scheduled trip for a route.
Stop
Represents an immutable location where vehicles pick up and drop off passengers at.
Vehicle
Represents public transit vehicle.
VehicleInfo
Real-time information about a vehicle.
VehicleType
Represents a type of public transit vehicle.
